properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 9 at 5:55AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
West winds of 30 to 35 mph sustained with gusts of 45 to 55 mph
are occurring this morning and are expected to continue the next
few hours before easing. This will create an increased blow off
and blow over risk for light weight and high profile vehicles.
Winds are expected to slowly ease after sunrise. If traveling
Interstate 80 this morning between Cheyenne and Laramie...be
prepared for sudden wind gusts that could push your vehicle off
the road. Keep a firm grip on your steering wheel and slow down
when encountering these strong winds.

NWSheadline: Strong Winds Over the Interstate 80 Summit Through 8 AM This Morning
